        "minPlayer": "2",
        "maxPlayer": "6",
        "minTime": "30",
        "maxTime": "30",
        "age": "7",
        "description": "Chinese Checkers, or Stern-Halma, is a version of Halma supporting up to six players. Parenthetically, it is neither Chinese nor is it Checkers. In many countries, it's known as Chinese Chess or China-Chess which is even less accurate and definitely shouldn't be confused with Xiangqi which is the true Chess variant from China.<br/><br/>Players jump over their own and/or their opponents' pieces with the objective of being the first to move all their pieces from one side to the opposing side.<br/><br/>Re-implements<br/><br/>    Halma<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>",
